701155f-a.title: Bronx: Grand Concourse - 164th Street
701155f-a.text:
1000 (empty 1ot), 10144 and 1022 Grand Concourse, at, adjoining and north of the N.E. corner of East 164th Street, showing the B. Richardson House (first one, No. 1014) and the Mrs. Roe House. The empty lot was occupied by the home of D.C. Weeks (map of 1885 by E. Robinson).
May 16, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
